algorithm
Class MonomSet

java.lang.Object
  algorithm.MonomSet
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable
public class MonomSet
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable

We first implement the Set of monoms. These sets are the big(!) sets which constist of all monoms matching some certain type. Thus the monoms are ordered only by their signature, not by their number of ones yet.
For example the set of X-X-XX contains:
0-0-00
0-1-00
0-1-10
1-0-01
1-1-11

The sorting of the subsets is delegate to the class MonomOnesSubset .It gets an object of this class as a parameter.
Then you can choose by the method MonomOneSubSet.getLiMk the subset of the original monomSet which has exactly k 1s.
